The paper deals with a sparse distributed estimation problem and proposes a new algorithm that combines the benefits of two existing algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to signal processing, machine learning, and optimization. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the estimation and processing of information signals. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for learning. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories as the paper deals with distributed estimation. cs.SP (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with signal processing algorithms.
